The article highlights the strong support for Gina Haspel as the next CIA Director. Various editorial boards and commentators argue for her swift confirmation, citing her qualifications, experience, and endorsements from both Democratic and Republican officials. They emphasize her long and distinguished career in the CIA, her proven administrative skills, and her ability to tackle complex threats facing the United States. Critics of Haspel's nomination are accused of hypocrisy and playing politics with national security. Overall, the article presents a consensus that Haspel is supremely qualified and deserving of bipartisan support.